deck: Short lived Canadian Comic Company
description:
P. L. Publisher was a short lived Canadian comic company that published 8 titles in 1951, none of which lasted longer than 3 issues.

They are different from many Canadian comic publishers in that all of their comics were in color while most of the rest of comics published in Canada at the time were in black & white.

Series included Border Patrol, Captain Rocket, Co-Ed Romances, Love Life, Red Arrow, Saari, Weird Adventures, and Western Frontier.
name: P. L. Publishers

deck:
Hibernia is a publisher from Co Mayo in the West of Ireland which specialises in reprints of classic British 80s comic strips.

Hibernia was set up by David McDonald.
description:
Hibernia have produced thirteen collections covering classic British boys comics.

Collections include classic reprints and 'comic archive' editions (featuring in-depth coverage of particular titles or themes).

  • Doomlord (from Eagle) (2005)
  • Thirteenth Floor (from Scream and Eagle) (2007)
  • One-Eyed Jack and the Death of Valiant ('comic archive') (Valiant and Eagle) (2012)
  • Beyond 2000AD ('comic archive') (2000AD) (2013)
  • The Tower King (from Eagle) (2014)
  • Baker's Half-Dozen (from Speed) (2014)
  • The Best of Library of Death (from Scream) (2014)
  • The Complete Dracula File (from Scream) (2015)
  • The House of Daemon (from Eagle) (2015)
  • Eagle Adventure Special (from Eagle) (2016)
  • It's Ghastly! - the untimely demise of Scream! ('comic archive') (Scream!) (2016)

The Thirteenth Floor collections

  • The Thirteenth Floor volume one (June 2014)
  • The Thirteenth Floor volume two (June 2014)

Available from their website http://www.comicsy.co.uk/hibernia/
name: Hibernia
